Program: Last Word
Title: 13/11/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00nrs1r
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 15 Nov 2009
Matthew Bannister presents the obituary series, analysing and celebrating the life stories of people who have recently died. The programme reflects on people of distinction and interest from many walks of life, some famous and some less well known. Marking the lives of epidemiologist, Professor Jeremy Morris; Chinese author and historian Nien Cheng; linguist and dialect expert Stanley Ellis; public campaigner Lady Tumim; and inventor, lawyer and 'Nessie' hunter, Robert Rines. Show less